On Wednesday, at the New York Times DealBook Summit, Jeff Bezos hinted at s=
ome new innovations he had planned for The Washington Post, which, as Bezos=
 acknowledged, =E2=80=9Cpunches above its weight=E2=80=9D when it comes to =
negative headlines. =E2=80=9CWe saved The Washington Post once, and we will=
 save it again,=E2=80=9D he said, noting that the paper had experienced six=
 or seven years of profitability before falling into its current funk. How?=
 =E2=80=9CI have a bunch of ideas,=E2=80=9D he said. =E2=80=9CStay tuned, w=
e=E2=80=99ll see.=E2=80=9D

In the more immediate future, as early as next week and certainly before th=
e end of the year, Post C.E.O. Will Lewis will name an executive editor for=
 the beleaguered mediaco=E2=80=94well, technically, the executive editor of=
 the first newsroom, for those following along. (You can study up here ( ht=
tps://puck.news/inside-the-coup-at-washington-post/?utm_campaign=3DIn+the+R=
oom+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%2812%2F4%2F24%29&utm_content=3DIn+The+Room+-+SUBSCRIBERS=
