e <i>New York Times </i>DealBook Summit, <b>Jeff Bezos </b>hinted at some n=
ew innovations he had planned for <i>The Washington Post</i>, which, as Bez=
os acknowledged, =E2=80=9Cpunches above its weight=E2=80=9D when it comes t=
o negative headlines. =E2=80=9CWe saved <i>The Washington Post </i>once, an=
d we will save it again,=E2=80=9D he said, noting that the paper had experi=
enced six or seven years of profitability before falling into its current f=
unk. How? =E2=80=9CI have a bunch of ideas,=E2=80=9D he said. =E2=80=9CStay=
 tuned, we=E2=80=99ll see.=E2=80=9D<br/><br/>In the more immediate future, =
as early as next week and certainly before the end of the year, <i>Post</i>=
 C.E.O. <b>Will Lewis </b>will name an executive editor for the beleaguered=
 mediaco=E2=80=94well, technically, the executive editor of the <i>first ne=
wsroom</i>, for those following along. (You can study up <u><a href=3D"http=
